X-Port is an application written by Dan Rowley, it was distributed by ICS <http://www.newts.com/newton].  It is now available on Kagi from Dan [https://order.kagi.com/cgi-bin/store.cgi?storeID=IC&&>.  It works with Windows and Macintosh computers.

From the package, the features are:
* Transfer Multiple Notes, Outlines, Lists, and Packages to and from your PC
* Import all contacts from any desktop PIM with ASCII text exporting
* Upload Newton screen shots as PICT or BMP files
* Download black-and-white PICT and BMP files for viewing/editing with Newtpaint

Requirements:
* Messagepad with Newton OS 2.0 or later
* 48k storage on the Newton
* Macintosh System 7.01 or later, uses Localtalk or serial connection
* PC with Windows 3.1 or later, compatible with Windows 95